---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Case Packing — Formic"
  description="Top-load and side-load case packing across SKUs. Consistent counts, predictable cycles, fewer line stops — deployed under Formic Full Service."
  ogTitle="Case Packing — Formic"
  ogDescription="Counts that hit, every time. Top-load and side-load case packing on a modular base."
>
  <link rel="canonical" href="https://formic.co/solutions/packing" slot="head" />

<div class="detail-bc">
  <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span><a href="/solutions">Solutions</a><span class="sep">/</span>Case Packing
</div>

<section class="detail-hero">
  <div class="si">
    <div class="slabel" style="color:var(--orange)">Case Packing</div>
    <h1>Counts that hit,<br><em>every time.</em></h1>
    <p class="lede">Top-load and side-load case packing across SKUs, formats, and pack patterns. Consistent counts, predictable cycle times, fewer line stops — and clean integration with the upstream filler and downstream sealer.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dark">
  <div class="detail-video wide">
    <div class="detail-video-frame">
      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline poster="/CasepackerPromoVideo_NoText_poster.jpg">
        <source src="/RFA_header.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
      </video>
      <span class="dv-fpo">FPO</span>
      <span class="dv-cap">Case packer · top-load configuration</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">01 — Why It Matters</div>
      <h2>Manual packing is <em>where lines drift</em>.</h2>
      <p>Manual case packing is variable by definition — counts shift between operators, between shifts, between Mondays and Fridays. That variability shows up in customer chargebacks and in the end-of-month yield report. Robotic case packing closes that gap.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Vision-verified counts on every cycle — no shortpacks, no overpacks</li>
        <li>Predictable cycle times feed predictable throughput up and down the line</li>
        <li>Fewer micro-stops between filler and sealer</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/#cta" class="larr">Scope my line →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/CasepackerPromoVideo_NoText.gif" alt="Case packer running" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Top-load · 60+ cycles/min</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block lgrey">
  <div class="db-grid flip">
    <div class="db-img">
      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline poster="/CasepackerPromoVideo_NoText_poster.jpg">
        <source src="/ATLAS_EOAT.webm" type="video/webm" />
      </video>
      <span class="img-cap">Side-load configuration</span>
    </div>
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">02 — Top-load + Side-load</div>
      <h2>Same base, <em>two formats</em>.</h2>
      <p>Top-load for bottles, jars, and tall packages. Side-load for bags, pouches, and wraps that benefit from horizontal collation. Same modular base — change the EOAT and the cycle pattern, ship the next SKU.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Top-load and side-load on the same modular base</li>
        <li>Fast SKU changeover — under 10 minutes for most format swaps</li>
        <li>Vision-guided count verification on every cycle</li>
        <li>Tool-less EOAT swaps for high-mix lines</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block white">
  <div class="db-grid">
    <div class="db-text">
      <div class="db-tag">03 — Specs</div>
      <h2>Designed for <em>SKU mix</em>.</h2>
      <p>Most CPG lines run 8–40 SKUs a week through a single packer. The system is built for that — fast changeover, software-driven format library, tool-free EOAT.</p>
      <ul class="feats">
        <li>Throughput: up to 60 cases/minute, format-dependent</li>
        <li>Case sizes: from RSC small parcel through bulk shippers</li>
        <li>Pack patterns: full library + custom patterns programmed at deployment</li>
        <li>Integration: direct handoff from filler, direct handoff to sealer + palletizer</li>
        <li>Safety: full guarding, light curtain access, ANSI/RIA R15.06 compliance</li>
      </ul>
      <a href="/#cta" class="larr">See it run →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="db-img"><img src="/Talos-0095.jpg" alt="Case packing cell with sealer" loading="lazy"/><span class="img-cap">Pack · seal · stage</span></div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-block dgrey">
  <div class="detail-video wide">
    <div class="detail-video-frame">
      <video autoplay muted loop playsinline poster="/Talos-0095.jpg">
        <source src="/RFA_header.mp4" type="video/mp4" />
      </video>
      <span class="dv-fpo">FPO</span>
      <span class="dv-cap">Pack + seal in one cell</span>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="detail-cta">
  <h2>Lock in your counts.<br><em>Lock in your line.</em></h2>
  <div class="btn-row">
    <a href="mailto:sales@formic.co" class="btn-ctadark">Get Started</a>
    <a href="/solutions" class="btn-ctawh">All Solutions</a>
  </div>
</section>
</Layout>
